		might need to do more work to mitigate false positives. For information, see Testing and tuning 
		your AWS WAF protections.
		The lower setting provides less stringent SQL injection detection, which also results in fewer 
		false positives. LOW can be a better choice for resources that have other protections against SQL 
		injection attacks or that have a low tolerance for false positives.
